// T109 — audited-corpus idempotence sweep for turboV.
// Recursive glob (`**/*.nsl`) handles upstream layouts that put
// NSL sources under `src/` (e.g. turboV).

// REQUIRES: audited-turboV

// Real upstream NSL surface exercises constructs that nsl-fmt's
// parser does not yet handle (post-M7-merge 2026-05-12). T2 owner:
// extend nsl-fmt's parser coverage; remove XFAIL when the
// M7-vendored turboV surface parses cleanly.
// XFAIL: *
// RUN: bash -c 'shopt -s globstar nullglob; for f in %S/../../../audited/turboV/**/*.nsl; do \
// RUN:   nsl-fmt --stdin < $f > %t.once && \
// RUN:   nsl-fmt --stdin < %t.once > %t.twice && \
// RUN:   cmp %t.once %t.twice || exit 1; \
// RUN: done'
